{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01MP74DAinWhS5aUmw5tTzKk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. The MongoDB replica set has been upgraded successfully.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Starting state:** 3-member replica set (`mongodb-replica-0/1/2`) in the `mongodb` namespace on `mongo:5.0.5`, FCV 5.0, with auth (keyFile + `admin-user`). pod-0 was PRIMARY.\n\n**What I did:**\n1. **Verified the baseline** — RS healthy, FCV already at 5.0 (the required prerequisite for upgrading to 6.0), and snapshotted the existing data (`testdb.data`, 1 document).\n2. **Rolling binary upgrade** — `kubectl set image statefulset/mongodb-replica mongod=mongo:6.0.5`. The StatefulSet's `RollingUpdate` strategy replaced pods in reverse-ordinal order (2→1→0), so secondaries upgraded first and the primary last — the MongoDB-recommended order. A clean election moved the PRIMARY to pod-2.\n3. **Waited for full rollout** — all 3 pods Ready on `mongo:6.0.5`, replica set health = 1 on every member.\n4. **Finalized feature compatibility** — ran `setFeatureCompatibilityVersion(\"6.0\")` on the primary.\n\n**Final verified state:**\n- All 3 members: version **6.0.5**, **FCV 6.0**, health 1 (1 PRIMARY + 2 SECONDARY).\n- **Data preserved** — `testdb.data` still holds the original document, unchanged (PVCs retained across the rolling restart).\n- No operators or CRDs used — plain StatefulSet rolling update."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":799,"cache_read_input_tokens":35530,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":799},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d49a1787-b36c-40da-930b-333e2fd2dd2f","uuid":"7d124f27-1851-44a8-ad98-ca147846bb9f","request_id":"req_011CcAwRHgJePAmaFvoA1K2S"}
